I"<<p>@CoreyRobin points to a tension that has defined conservatism from the  get-go, between two competing conceptions of virtue and nobility: one  defined by political and military distinction and another by  entrepreneurial  acumen and accumulated wealth. Robin parses how Trump  fits into this dynamic history, in part by taking a look back to seminal  conservative thinkers like Edmund Burke and Friedrich Hayek. Thanks to  our sponsors at Verso. Check out <a href="versobooks.com/books/2571-out-of-the-wreckage">Out of the Wreckage: A New Politics for an Age of Crisis by George Monbiot</a> and support us with $ at <a href="http://www.patreon.com/TheDig">patreon.com/TheDig</a> 
